{
  "name": "Illusionist Research",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "icons/magic/symbols/fleur-de-lis-yellow.webp",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Category: Skill</p><p>You have begun to find some truth in the world of illusions and Genjutsu, finding its origins to be darker and more sinister than you once thought.</p><p>You gain the following benefits:</p><p>• Increase your Intelligence or Wisdom by 1, to a maximum of 20.</p><p>• You gain proficiency in the Illusions skill.</p><p>If you are already proficient, you instead gain Mastery.</p><p>• When you would make an Identify Genjutsu check, you reduce the DC, by 5.</p><p>• If you would attempt a Read the Enemy check, on a creature casting a Genjutsu, you no longer need to see a creatures using Handsigns to attempt this check, and you gain a +2 bonus to saving throws made against this Genjutsu's casting, until the beginning of your next turn.</p><p>• You reduce the downtime needed to learn Genjutsu using the self-taught method by an amount equal to the rank of the jutsu.</p><p>(D-Rank: 1, C-Rank: 2, B-Rank: 3, A-Rank: 4, S-Rank: 5.)</p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
